8 tablespoons butter
2 tablespoons mirin
2 large onion, quartered and thinly sliced
2 large tart apple, peeled, cored, finely diced
1 head of cabbage, coarsely chopped or shredded, about 8 cups
1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper
5 tablespoons brown rice vinegar
1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar
salt, to taste

In a Dutch oven, heat butter over low heat; add onion and apple; saut√© for about 7 to 10 minutes, or until soft. Add cabbage, pepper, vinegar, and mirin; toss to blend well. 

Cover tightly and place in over for 30 minutes at 425F. Reduce heat to 375F and bake for another hour, or until the cabbage is thoroughly tender; stir occasionally as it cooks. Add salt to taste. 


Serves 8.

Source: 
  based off of # http://southernfood.about.com/od/cabbagerecipes/r/bl70115a.htm
  Tangy Braised Cabbage
  By Diana Rattray, About.com Guide
